{"actor":"actor_planning_lane","at":"2026-06-11T22:44:37.463Z","command":"topogram sdlc new goal_branch_packet semantic_diff_fact_inventory . --branch-ref goal/semantic-diff-fact-inventory --with-plan --actor actor_planning_lane --name Remogram Semantic Diff Fact Inventory Foundation --description Draft Intent Packet for Remogram fact-layer support of Topogram Git-as-semantic-diff-database ref inventory. Remogram exposes provider-neutral forge/ref/change-request facts; Topogram remains SDLC semantic authority. Planning-only until explicit approval. --problem Topogram branch workcycle and semantic diff need a provider-neutral ref/change-request fact inventory, but Remogram today exposes only six read/plan commands without structured ref inventory or semantic-diff-oriented aggregation. Agents cannot compose observer snapshots or Topogram queries from stable remogram packets alone. --solution Six serialized waves: (1) fact packet model and trust boundaries, (2) git/ref inventory provider core, (3) change-request/check/merge-plan aggregation, (4) observer snapshot integration, (5) Topogram consumer contract examples, (6) tests/fixtures/docs/smoke validation. Read-only facts and contracts first; implementation waves after plan approval and per-wave claim. --rabbit-holes Mutation/write commands; SDLC fields in remogram output; Topogram runtime dependency in remogram-core; full semantic prompt firewall; rewriting forge-trust archaeology; live-network default tests. --no-go-areas packages implementation in draft PR; hand-editing command-owned sidecar status; committing topo to remo; approving goal or ACs in draft PR; duplicating Topogram queue/lifecycle semantics in remogram packets. --affects cap_forge_remote_ops --priority high --architecture-pattern contract_boundary --architecture-pattern fail_closed_gate --architecture-pattern command_owned_mutation --write --json","content_hashes_by_record":[{"record_id":"pitch_semantic_diff_fact_inventory","sha256":"ffb79d6fb31c602a2